Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

2024-12-19

Vossia cuspidata

Photo by Mike Wood, licensed under CC-BY-NC 4.0

Assembly is allelic, and the genome is tetraploid. It has a haploid genome size of 900 Mb, and has 20 haploid chromosomes.

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Vossia cuspidata from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Highlighted Figure 1

Figure 1 from the main text, with Vossia cuspidata highlighted with colored points.

Highlighted Figure 2

Figure 2 from the main text, with Vossia cuspidata highlighted with colored points.

Dotplot of Vossia cuspidata vs. Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Vossia cuspidata along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Vossia cuspidata is a tetraploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 4 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Vossia cuspidata

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Vossia cuspidata along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Vossia cuspidata is a tetraploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 4 lines for each subgenome.
